TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {9922=Another Paul Rudolph house is under imminent threat of extinction in Westport, CT!  The Micheels House at 16 Minuteman Hill is one of scores of houses faced with demolition in the land of the ultra-rich in Fairfiled County, CT, where Location-Location-Location trumps historical preservation.  CIMA is pleased to host guest lecturer Nepal Asatthawasi, who runs the Paul Rudolph Foundation, for their December meeting.  Ms. Asattawasi will be accompanied by a Foundation architect/advisor and will speak on the value of Rudolph's work and its meaning for current and future architects.  Nepal Asatthawasi of the Paul Rudolph Foundation.  Paul Rudolph: Implications for the Future.  Tuesday, December 12, at 6:15 PM.  Perkins + Eastman, 115 Fifth Avenue, New York, NY.  1.5 CES Lus.  Members free, Non-Members $10, 9757=Published by info on Wed, 2006-12-06 18:24}
